      {
        "id": "0b447ce2e6e0c1a4f039b1e2e721729deaae90c8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-12 13:20:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n\nI assume the idea here is to easily track a commit on which the image is based. And if yes maybe (if possible) the snapshot image name itself should also contain short commit sha?\n\nIf adding those labels is widely expected property of an image by community maybe it should be configured/enforced on oparent level (if applicable)?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "28d9f65bc62d5a03e29b05e152e6b78cdb93a6b5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-12 13:28:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nBTW how about using Gerrit's Change-ID instead of both branch and commit sha?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "c0226f72803b2f104d91fbea6378511a4a9015fc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5,
          "name": "Christophe Closset",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "christophe.closset@intl.att.com",
          "username": "ChrisC"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-12 14:36:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI think the idea is trying to follow what the base image are trying to do, if they set labels, our derived images should do the same. So yes there may be a broader discussion on what labels we want, how we want them etc.\n\nOn using the Change-ID, I'm not fully sure, we can add it as well if needed but my thinking was to stick with git attributes to stay portable on other envs.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "cdfecf1f2a98ad8e0107fcea26b756f447ea86b8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2319,
          "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
          "username": "sdesbure"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-15 06:37:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n\nThanks @Christophe,\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/sdc/sdc-docker-base/+/108763 should be rebased on top of this one and using the two labels created here IMHO",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "d2920083f575f577e4e503344cd4050382d5a18e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2319,
          "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
          "username": "sdesbure"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-15 06:38:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> I think the idea is trying to follow what the base image are trying to do, if they set labels, our derived images should do the same. So yes there may be a broader discussion on what labels we want, how we want them etc.\n> \n> On using the Change-ID, I'm not fully sure, we can add it as well if needed but my thinking was to stick with git attributes to stay portable on other envs.\n\nI agree with Christophe, the Gerrit change id is gerrit specific whereas the commit id (+ branch) is generic",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
